overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming to transform its generic look into a more polished
  and calming experience. The agent began by analyzing the existing codebase,
  identifying key areas for improvement such as the color palette, component
  styling, and overall layout. A new sleep-themed color palette was introduced,
  along with custom CSS utilities for gradients and shadows. Core UI components
  like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and progress bars were enhanced with
  improved visual feedback and modern styling. The main questionnaire form and
  intro section were redesigned to be more engaging and visually appealing.
  During the review, a console error related to null input values was identified
  and fixed by ensuring inputs receive empty strings instead of null. Following
  user feedback, the agent further refined the styling by standardizing alert
  colors across all sections, increasing the visual definition of section
  borders, and ensuring all report section card headers and text colors
  consistently adhered to the new sleep theme. The entire process involved
  iterative improvements, code modifications, and browser-based verification,
  culminating in a cohesive and aesthetically pleasing application.
